# Exercise 005 - Create a user that can view an existing project

1) As user "developer" create a project named "my-shared-project" and deploy a
   tomcat application in it;

2) As the admin user, create a user named "test1";

3) Login as "test1" and try to switch to the previously created project;

4) As admin user add role "view" to user test1 for the project 
   "my-shared-project";

5) Check that now you are capable of viewing the contents of the project but
   not to deploy anything new;
